<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ripen" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ripen,</orth> 1) trans. to make ripe, to mature; absol.: <cit><quote>summer's --ing breath,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.121" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 2, 121</bibl></cit>. With an obj.: <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.43" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 3, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.227" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 227</bibl>. Partic. <cit><quote>--ed:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 116</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.99" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 4, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 3, 14</bibl>.<lb />2) intr. to grow ripe, to be matured: <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.48" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 3, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 1, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.357" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 357</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 103</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>